Package: spharmlithic
Title: Spherical Harmonic Analysis of Lithic Morphology and Flaking Scar Patterns
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R:
    person("Peiyuan", "Xiao", , "pyxiao@uw.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A complete toolkit for the geometric alignment, directional
    statistics, and spherical harmonic analysis of three-dimensional
    lithic flaking scar orientation data. Provides two alignment pipelines
    (SVD and Lin 2024), classical orientation statistics (SPI with
    Clarkson length weighting, elongation/isotropy from the orientation
    tensor), and a Python-backed spherical harmonic pipeline (von
    Mises-Fisher kernel density estimation followed by Driscoll-Healy
    spherical harmonic expansion via pyshtools), supporting both
    direction-vector and mesh-based inputs.
